                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/121.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hanna</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-30T14:00:00-06:41">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 30, 1914, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s June 18, 6 p.m. Foreign Secretary Fabela replies that First Chief of
                    the Constitutionalists has directed General Aguilar that he should report to him
                    about the matter and recommended with much interest that he should impart
                    protection to the property referred to belonging to Americans in the
                    Panueo-Topila region.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
